<h2>REST API</h2>
This tool provides a set of REST API endpoints that can be useful for testing purposes.


<h4>Endpoints</h4>
The following endpoints are defined:
<br />
<a href="/api/customers">GET /api/customers</a> - Get a list all customers.
<br />
<a href="/api/customers/2">GET /api/customers/2</a> - Get a specific customer (1-100).
<br />
<a href="/api/CustomersSlow/2">GET /api/customersSlow/2</a> - Get a specific customer (1-100), ID=10 takes 1s, others 20ms.
<br />
<a href="/api/echo">GET /api/echo</a> - Echo back the received response headers.
<br />
<a href="/api/time">GET /api/time</a> - Returns the current time.
<br />
<a href="/api/cpu">GET /api/cpu</a> - Start consuming max CPU for 1 minute
<br />
<a href="/api/memory">GET /api/memory</a> - Start consuming as much memory as possible for 1 minute.
